author: gstein
msg: Switch the locking code over to the new XML processing.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/locks.c:
(lock_state_e): drop enum/typedef name. rename NONE to INITIAL. add
MULTISTATUS, RESPONSE, PROPSTATE, and HREF states. rename COMMENT
to OWNER (the latter is the element; the former is the lock
structure's member)
(lock_info_t): add INNER_HANDLER/BATON so we can properly wrap the
expat parser with a bit more response handling
(push_state, start_lock, end_lock, cdata_lock): removed. obsolete.
(locks_ttable): new transition table.
(locks_closed): new callback to process the state closures
(determine_error): the handler's server_error will always be NULL
since run_one() deals with it. do not wrap our generic error
around an existing error from run_one().
(handle_lock): adjust the baton. defer to the inner handler/baton.
(svn_ra_serf__get_lock): for safety, copy the PATH parameter into
the result pool. switch over to the new xml processing.
(svn_ra_serf__lock): switch over to the new xml processing.
